## Summary

The `doey add-window --task-id` pipeline works correctly end-to-end. The flag is parsed in `doey.sh:384`, passed through `add_dynamic_team_window()` (doey-team-mgmt.sh:1126), and written to `team_*.env` via `write_team_env()` (doey-team-mgmt.sh:22). The `_name_team_window()` function (doey-team-mgmt.sh:835) reads TASK_ID from the env file and uses it in the window name. Task binding (`doey task update --field team --value W${NEW_W}`) is **documented in the Taskmaster agent** but is **NOT automated** in the shell code — the Taskmaster must call it manually after spawn.

